## Sprint 2 (Sep 7 - Sep 20)
### Feedback as a Two-Way Skill

**[Sep 7] Team Meeting**  
Through more exercises and collaborative efforts towards developing workflows and documentation, we honed our production line. This marked a shift: I began giving as much feedback as I received. Nick pushed us to explain *why* we made certain choices, not just present results. Defending my decisions respectfully, rather than defaulting to agreement, felt like a step into professional collaboration.

**[Sep 14] Halfway Review**  
Patterns emerged among the reviews from outside the audio team - some feedback was actionable; some was purely subjective. I began mentally categorising notes into *must-change*, *worth-trying*, and *leave-for-now*. This kept iteration efficient and confidences intact. I also paid closer attention to how others reacted to critique, adjusting my tone and language accordingly as some would take better to bluntness and others a gentle suggestion.

*(Motivic exercise pieces)*
